			    STPJS 252</div>
  <p class="cont">he put his hand unto; it was because he and his family obeyed the counsel of the Lord.<span class="footRef">1</span></p>
  <p class="std">When Egypt was under the superintendence of Joseph<span class="footRef">2</span> it prospered, because he was taught of
  God;<span class="footRef">3</span> when they oppressed the Israelites,<span class="footRef">4</span> destruction came upon them.<span class="footRef">5</span> When the children of Israel
  were chosen with Moses at their head, they were to be a peculiar people,<span class="footRef">6</span> among whom God should
  place His name;<span class="footRef">7</span> their motto was: &ldquo;The Lord is our lawgiver; the Lord is our Judge; the Lord is our
  King; and He shall reign over us.&rdquo;<span class="footRef">8</span> While in this state they might truly say, &ldquo;Happy is that people,
  whose God is the Lord.&rdquo;<span class="footRef">9</span> Their government was a theocracy; they had God to make their laws,<span class="footRef">10</span> and
  men chosen by Him to administer them;<span class="footRef">11</span> He was their God, and they were His people.<span class="footRef">12</span> Moses
  received the word of the Lord from God Himself;<span class="footRef">13</span> he was the mouth of God to Aaron,<span class="footRef">14</span> and Aaron
  taught the people,<span class="footRef">15</span> in both civil and ecclesiastical affairs; they were both one, there was no
  distinction; so will it be when the purposes of God shall be accomplished:<span class="footRef">16</span> when &ldquo;the Lord shall
  be King over the whole earth&rdquo;<span class="footRef">17</span> and &ldquo;Jerusalem His throne.&rdquo;<span class="footRef">18</span> &ldquo;The law shall go forth from Zion,
  and the word of the Lord from Jerusalem.&rdquo;<span class="footRef">19</span></p>
  <div class="topic">Universal Peace to Come from God</div>
  <p class="std">This is the only thing that can bring about the &ldquo;restitution of all things spoken of by all the holy
  Prophets since the world was&rdquo;<span class="footRef">20</span>&mdash;&ldquo;the dispensation of the fullness of times, when God shall gather
  together all things in one.&rdquo;<span class="footRef">21</span> Other attempts to promote universal peace and happiness in the human
  family have proved abortive; every effort has failed; every plan and design has fallen to the ground;
  it needs the wisdom of God,<span class="footRef">22</span> the intelligence of God,<span class="footRef">23</span> and the power of God to accomplish this.
  The world has had a fair trial for six thousand years; the Lord will try the seventh thousand
  Himself;<span class="footRef">24</span> &ldquo;He whose right it is,<span class="footRef">25</span> will possess the kingdom,<span class="footRef">26</span> and reign until He has put all things
  under His feet;&rdquo;<span class="footRef">27</span> iniquity will hide its hoary head,<span class="footRef">28</span> Satan will be bound,<span class="footRef">29</span> and the works of
  darkness destroyed;<span class="footRef">30</span> righteousness will be put to the line, and judgment to the plummet,<span class="footRef">31</span> and &ldquo;he
  that fears the Lord will alone be exalted in that day.&rdquo;<span class="footRef">32</span> To bring about this state of things, there must
  of necessity be great confusion among the nations of the earth; &ldquo;distress of nations with
  perplexity.&rdquo;<span class="footRef">33</span> Am I asked what is the cause of</p>
